- Tue 9 Jun 2020. External situation report 96
[WHO, abridged, edited]
https://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/handle/10665/332320/SITREP_EVD_DRC_20200610-eng.pdf?ua=1

Data as reported by 8 Jun 2020:

The ebolavirus disease (EVD) outbreak in Equateur Province, Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), continues since its declaration on 1 Jun 2020 by the Ministry of Health. Since our last situation report on 2 Jun 2020 (external situation report 95), 4 additional confirmed EVD cases and 4 deaths have been reported. As of 8 Jun 2020, a total of 12 EVD cases (9 confirmed and 3 probable), including 8 deaths (case fatality ratio, 66.7%), have been reported from 6 health areas in 3 health zones. Of the 8 deaths, 4 occurred in the community. The case fatality ratio among confirmed cases is 55.6% (5 deaths/9 confirmed cases). Two health workers are among the confirmed cases since the start of the outbreak, 18.2% of all cases. Of the 4 confirmed cases still alive, 2 are under treatment in the Ebola treatment centre and 2 are in the community [see updated numbers under Case updates - Mod.LK].

The health zones reporting EVD cases are Mbandaka (6 confirmed, 3 probable, 3 deaths), Wangata (2 confirmed, 1 death) and Bikoro (1 confirmed and 1 death).

Sequencing of the initial confirmed specimen (swab) conducted at the Institute National de Recherche Biomedicale (INRB), Kinshasa, indicated the Zaire ebolavirus isolated in Equateur Province is not linked to the outbreak in eastern DRC. Additional samples have been sent to the INRB for sequencing. Investigations around the origin of this outbreak are ongoing.

As of 8 Jun 2020, a total of 289 contacts have been identified for follow up, of which 255 (88%) were seen on the reporting day.

--
