[See ProMED-mail Ebola update (25): Congo DR (EQ, NK) cases, response WHO, new spillover 20200606.7432964. The sequencing analysis of virus from the current outbreak suggests the virus strain likely represents a new spillover event and the 11th EVD outbreak in the DRC, the 3rd outbreak in 2 years.

Also see WHO statement at https://www.afro.who.int/news/no-link-between-two-ongoing-ebola-outbreaks-democratic-republic-congo:

Note to Editors - key figures
-----------------------------
Recent Ebola outbreaks in DRC
- 11th outbreak: Mbandaka, Equateur province
Ongoing. Declared on 1 Jun 2020.
12 cases (9 confirmed, 3 probable); 8 deaths.

-10th outbreak: North Kivu, South Kivu and Ituri provinces
Ongoing. Declared on 1 Aug 2018.
3463 cases (3317 confirmed and 146 probable). Of these, 2280 people died and 1171 survived.

- 9th outbreak: Mbandaka, Equateur province
Declared on 8 May 2018 and ended on 24 Jul 2018.
54 cases (38 confirmed and 16 probable). Of those, 33 died and 21 survived.
- Mod.LK]

